SLAs = Server-Level Agreements

#Cloud Resource Responsability
-The combinationof Data Plan & Management Plan depende of the SLA (Iaas, PaaS, SaaS)


##Data Plane 
	Workload (More emphasize in Cloud)  (+ Client Responsability) (DP)
	Services (More emphasize in Cloud) (MP)
	Virtual Machine (More emphasize in Cloud) (SLA)

#Management 
	Management Plane (Only in Cloud)
	Virtualization: Platform, Maintenance and Licensing
	Physical Infrastructure: Power, Network, Storage and Racks
	Physical Facility: Costs of Space, Physical Security and Personnel (+ Vendor Responsability)

#Cloud SLAs
##AWS
-Baseline EC2 – 99.99% Uptime
-https://aws.amazon.com/legal/service-level-agreements/

##Azure
-Baseline virtual machine – 99.99% uptime*
-https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/support/legal/sla/

##Google Cloud Platform
-Baseline virtual machine – 99.99% uptime*
-https://cloud.google.com/terms/sla

*Azure and Google virtual machines must have multiple instances in different availability zones to qualify for 99.99% SLA.

